## Step 3 — Implement in TwoFactorAuthServiceImpl

File: `src/main/java/com/bukuwarung/fsbnplservice/service/impl/TwoFactorAuthServiceImpl.java`

Add constants:
```java
private static final String PATH_TWOFA_OTP_SEND = "/api/v3/auth/twofa/otp/send";
private static final String PATH_TWOFA_OTP_VERIFY = "/api/v3/auth/twofa/otp/verify";
```

Implement `sendOtpForPinSetup` (PUT or POST as auth service expects — use POST):
```java
@Override
public void sendOtpForPinSetup(String userId, String email, String phone, String method) {
  String url = multiAuthBaseUrl + PATH_TWOFA_OTP_SEND;
  Map<String, String> body = new HashMap<>();
  if (email != null) body.put("email", email);
  if (phone != null) body.put("phone", phone);
  if (method != null) body.put("method", method);
  body.put("source", LENDING_PIN_SOURCE);
  try {
    restTemplate.exchange(url, HttpMethod.POST, new HttpEntity<>(body, buildHeaders(userId)), Void.class);
  } catch (HttpClientErrorException | RestClientException e) {
    log.error("Error sending OTP for userId={}: {}", userId, e.getMessage());
    throw new TwoFAServiceUnavailableException("Auth service error sending OTP", e);
  }
}
```

Implement `verifyOtpForPinSetup`:
```java
@Override
public TwoFAVerifyOtpResponseDto verifyOtpForPinSetup(String userId, String otp, String email) {
  String url = multiAuthBaseUrl + PATH_TWOFA_OTP_VERIFY;
  Map<String, String> body = new HashMap<>();
  body.put("otp", otp);
  if (email != null) body.put("email", email);
  try {
    ResponseEntity<TwoFAVerifyOtpResponseDto> response = restTemplate.exchange(
        url, HttpMethod.POST, new HttpEntity<>(body, buildHeaders(userId)), TwoFAVerifyOtpResponseDto.class);
    TwoFAVerifyOtpResponseDto responseBody = response.getBody();
    if (responseBody == null) throw new TwoFAServiceUnavailableException("Empty OTP verify response", null);
    return responseBody;
  } catch (HttpClientErrorException e) {
    log.error("Error verifying OTP for userId={}: {}", userId, e.getMessage());
    throw new TwoFAServiceUnavailableException("Auth service error verifying OTP", e);
  } catch (RestClientException e) {
    log.error("Network error verifying OTP for userId={}: {}", userId, e.getMessage());
    throw new TwoFAServiceUnavailableException("Auth service unavailable", e);
  }
}
```

